explanation: To determine whether MHD_str_unquote constitutes unreachable code in the project you must know whether it is ever reachable from any program/library entry point. The direct callers (get_rq_param_unquoted_copy_z, get_rq_nc, get_unquoted_param, get_unquoted_param_copy) are required so the analyzer can see how/if MHD_str_unquote is invoked. Their callers (get_rq_uname, MHD_digest_auth_get_request_info3, digest_auth_check_all_inner) are required because reachability must be traced transitively up to exported/public API or program entry points; if all chains originating at these callers are themselves never reachable, then MHD_str_unquote would be unreachable. Inspecting these symbols (their definitions, visibility, and their own callers) lets the next agent decide whether any call chain leads from an entry point to MHD_str_unquote (or whether the function is effectively dead/unreachable).
